The paper discusses secure multi-party numerical computation in a Peer-to-Peer network, which involves topics related to cryptography, distributed computing, and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
